# Windows 11 Upgrade & Endpoint Security Compliance Project

## Overview

During my Systems and Security Support internship at Linamar, I independently led a Windows 11 upgrade and endpoint security compliance initiative involving over 100 corporate devices.

The organization maintained a large inventory of Windows 10 systems, many of which were inactive, unidentified, or had not yet been assessed for Windows 11 readiness. The objective of this project was to identify eligible devices, improve endpoint visibility, and ensure systems met modern security requirements before deployment.

## Objectives

* Identify Windows 10 endpoints requiring upgrades.
* Validate hardware compatibility for Windows 11.
* Improve endpoint security posture through compliance verification.
* Upgrade devices while minimizing disruption to end users.
* Ensure security features such as TPM and Secure Boot were properly configured.

## Technologies Used

* Windows 10
* Windows 11
* SentinelOne
* Microsoft Endpoint Management Tools
* BIOS/UEFI Configuration
* TPM (Trusted Platform Module)
* Secure Boot

## Project Responsibilities

### Asset Discovery and Identification

Using internal endpoint management and security tools, including SentinelOne, I conducted system scans and reviewed compliance reports to identify Windows 10 devices across the environment.

This process helped locate systems that were:

* Eligible for Windows 11 upgrades
* Inactive or unmanaged
* Missing required security configurations
* Approaching end-of-support requirements

### Upgrade Planning and Validation

Before deployment, each device was assessed for Windows 11 compatibility. Hardware requirements were validated, including:

* TPM availability and activation
* Secure Boot configuration
* Processor compatibility
* System health and readiness

Any identified issues were documented and remediated before proceeding with the upgrade.

### Windows 11 Deployment

I successfully performed Windows 11 upgrades and image deployments on more than 100 devices.

The deployment process included:

* Operating system upgrades
* Driver validation
* Security configuration verification
* Post-upgrade testing
* User readiness checks

### Security Compliance Verification

Following each deployment, security controls were reviewed to ensure compliance with organizational standards.

Key security checks included:

* TPM enabled and functioning
* Secure Boot enabled
* Endpoint protection operational
* Device successfully reporting to management and security platforms

## Results

* Successfully upgraded and deployed Windows 11 on 100+ corporate devices.
* Improved endpoint visibility by identifying unmanaged and inactive assets.
* Enhanced organizational security posture through TPM and Secure Boot validation.
* Supported compliance and modernization efforts by migrating systems from Windows 10 to Windows 11.
* Completed the project independently from asset identification through deployment and verification.

